figgy.title: Failing test on circleci nightly build
Update EligibleItemService to look for patron_group_charged on the item level
Update the EligibleItemService to look for patron_group_charged: "CDL"
Update PULFA source_metadata_identifiers to ASpace IDs

comments.body:
## Technical Implementation

`RemoteRecord.retrieve` should check to see if a thing looks like an ASpace ID (I think they all contain the string "aspace"), and if so spin up a new `ArchiveSpaceRecord`.

`ArchiveSpaceRecord` 

https://archivesspace.github.io/archivesspace/api/#get-an-ead-representation-of-a-resource211 has some documentation on how to get a record out of ASpace. We might be able to not get the EAD representation and just pull the JSON (which I think is the same path but no `.xml` at the end.) Need a spike to try it out when we have real data in there.

pulfalight.title: Provide an option to print/download the finding aid in its entirety

comments.body:
Update: ArchivesSpace can generate PDFs out-of-the box. However, we need to evaluate how accessible they are. The best practice for "printing" use cases is to use a Print Stylesheet.

We also decided to have a "Print this Finding Aid" button on every page of the collection.

pulfalight.title: Load fixture documents when starting solr
Implement collection-level badges indicating the access permissions for the resource

comments.body: Propose using the [LUX Tag element](https://pulibrary.github.io/lux/docs/#/Elements/Tag) for the badges.
**Note for reviewers**. If you use lando, you'll have to run `lando stop` and then `bundle exec solr start` to get the fixtures loaded correctly.
